  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Byluru Thippaiah @ Byaluru Thippaiah @ Nayakara Thippaiah versus State of Karnataka pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_7_550_567','2025INSC862'); ><font size='4'> <strong>BYLURU THIPPAIAH @ BYALURU THIPPAIAH @ NAYAKARA THIPPAIAH<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF KARNATAKA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 550</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 862</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002922025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANJAY KAROL, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards commutation of the death sentence awarded to the appellant for committing brutal murder of his wife, sister-in- law and his three children. Headnotes&dagger; Sentence/Sentencing &ndash; Death sentence &ndash; Commutation murder by the appellant of his wife, sister-in- law and his three children &ndash; Motive was that the appellant accused his wife and sister-in-law of being promiscuous and that he had not fathered the three children &ndash; Trial court convicted the appellant for the offence punishable u/s.302<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 16-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2490/2023</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Case Partly allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 3 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_7_550_567','2025INSC862','S')><i <i class='fas fa-co